{#- Temporary Grafana datasource that points at the NATIVE Loki instance
    during the blue/green rollback window (feature 087-containerize-services,
    T037 sub-step 6, FR-018).

    The native Loki is moved to port {{ native_archive_port }} via a
    Salt-managed config override so the containerized Loki can take over
    the primary port. This datasource gives Grafana Explore read access to
    historical logs on the native instance for the duration of the window.

    This file is ONLY deployed while features.containers.loki is true and
    the rollback window is open (cutover_date .. cutover_date + 7 days).
    T054 removes both this file AND the port override atomically with the
    native Loki pkg.removed — leaving either behind is a spec violation.
-#}
apiVersion: 1
datasources:
  - uid: loki-native-archive
    name: "Loki (native, pre-cutover archive, expires {{ cutover_expiry }})"
    type: loki
    access: proxy
    url: http://127.0.0.1:{{ native_archive_port }}
    isDefault: false
    editable: false
    jsonData:
      timeout: 60
